# Documentation Consistency

- When adding or changing a feature, update `prd.md`, `mvp.md`, `plan.md`, and `Progress.md` together.
- Screen / UX IA changes also update `ekran-haritasi.md` and `designsystem.md` (§28A).
- Data-platform / lab changes also update `veri-mimarisi.md`.
- Field hardware / IoT node changes also update `iot-mimarisi.md`.
- `Progress.md` is the source of truth for implementation status.
- `canvas.md` / `projeanalizi.md` are strategy/vision — do not treat them as MVP scope.
- Do not add MVP-out-of-scope features (satellite, drone, fertilizer **prescription**, yield).
- Lab report upload is in-scope as **P1** (units + user confirm); OCR auto-save and lab APIs are P2.
- Mark completed checklist items in `Progress.md` when implementation lands.
- Keep document filenames as `plan.md` and `Progress.md` (not legacy aliases).
- Prefer Recharts over Plotly in tech docs for the Next.js stack.
- Keep README / AGENTS folder trees aligned with the real repo (docs live at repo root).
- Mobile is responsive of the same screen ID — do not count separate mobile screens toward the 38.
